						<summary>

						<p>This is very much damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 960 Bahudhānya, • • • • Dakshiṇāyana-saṅkrānti</hi> probably corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1038 June 25, Sunday.</hi> It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalladēva.</hi> A gift of 50 <hi rend="italic">mattars</hi> of land with a garden is stated to have been made in the presence of the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Sōgeyūr</hi> when <hi rend="bold">Udayādityadēva</hi> was ruling some <hi rend="italic">nāḍu</hi> (name lost) and <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamallanirmaḍi-No[ḷamba]</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Māseyavāḍi hundred-and-forty.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
